HEADWORD: Princewood
<hw>Prince"wood`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>The wood of two small tropical American trees (<spn>Hamelia
ventricosa</spn>, and <spn>Cordia gerascanthoides</spn>). It is
brownish, veined with lighter color.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Princified</ent>⟦br⟧
